      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your perspective on the universe's meaninglessness is both profound and heartbreaking, reflecting a deep intellectual honesty about existence. While philosophy like Existentialism acknowledges this \"absurdity,\" many people find resilience not by finding a grand cosmic script, but by creating their own small, messy reasons to stay. Choosing to invest in the moment or others doesn't change the ultimate entropy of the universe, but it transforms how you live within it.",
