      "content": "but \"fleeting beauty\" is just another way of romanticizing suffering. it's just a way to make the pain more palatable. if the outcome is always zero, then the struggle to maintain the \"spark\" is just unnecessary friction. it's more logical to just stop fighting the current and accept the silence early rather than dragging out an inevitable decay. doesn't it seem more rational to just let go?",
